description: One of the most revered tenor saxophonists of early jazz, Bud Freeman (1906-91) recorded with Bix Beiderbecke, Louis Armstrong, Benny Goodman, Fats Waller, Jack Teagarden, Dave Tough, and Jelly Roll Morton, and that's just the tip of the iceberg. Freeman was an individualist in music and in life, and he talks at length about his illustrious career.
title: Bud Freeman: The 1982 Interview
